Inputs: All fields listed in the Data Dictionary below.
Validation: Verify fields (e.g., account number format, IFSC/SWIFT), check for existing accounts, ensure account status is active.
Output: Confirmation message, account linked to customer profile.
FR2: View/Edit Bank Account
Actor: Customer/Bank Staff.
Description: Users can view linked bank accounts and edit details (with appropriate permissions/verification).
Inputs: Select account, enter updated details.
Validation: Same as FR1; enforce security protocols for editing.
Output: Updated account details, confirmation.
FR3: Delete/Deactivate Bank Account
Actor: Bank Staff (for deactivation), Customer (for linking/unlinking).
Description: Remove/disable a bank account from a customer's profile.
Validation: Check for pending transactions, minimum balance requirements.
Output: Account removed/deactivated. 
3. Data Dictionary (for Bank Details)
Account Holder Name: Full legal name (String, Max 100 chars).
Account Number: Unique identifier (Numeric/Alphanumeric, Length [e.g., 9-18], Validation [e.g., Luhn check]).
Account Type: Savings (SB), Current (CA) (Enum: SB, CA).
Bank Name: Name of the bank (String, Max 100 chars).
Branch Name: Branch location (String, Max 100 chars).
IFSC/SWIFT Code: Indian Financial System Code/SWIFT (Alphanumeric, Specific format, e.g., 11 chars for IFSC).
MICR Code: Magnetic Ink Character Recognition (Numeric, 9 digits).
Address: Branch address (String). 
4. Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)
Security: Encrypt sensitive data (account numbers), use multi-factor authentication for changes, comply with PCI DSS/local regulations.
Performance: <2 sec for data retrieval, <5 sec for saving/validation.
Usability: Intuitive forms, clear error messages. 
5. External Interface Requirements
Core Banking System (CBS): APIs for real-time balance checks, transaction processing.
Notifications: SMS/Email gateway for alerts. 
